<br>
I think when people buy/sell platinum, it contributes to the decline of quality people on this server. People sell the platinum for cash, and it contributes to people coming to FV for the No Drop rules as they can get better equipment for their cash here. That’s what keeps the ebay trade going and directly affects the quality of EQ for players on our server. <br>
<br>
Furthermore, the point of being in a guild is to work together to accomplish things. Why would the guild ever work to raid a target if the members are just going to buy platinum and get the drop without raiding? What’s the point in moving to the next tier if you are just going to buy the items past that? If it’s not any fun to work your way up, then why be in a guild that is full of members wanting to work their way up? <br>
<br>
When a person works to get plat and buys something, that’s part of the ingame economy. When a person buys plat to buy items, that’s helping people that don’t care at all about the quality of the server. <br>
<br>
I know the ingame economy is broken because there is no limit on how much money is on the server. Also, there aren’t enough ways to pull money back out of the game to get the ingame economy stable. Think of how rarely you buy anything from vendors. Most money drops of mobs and never gets out of circulation.<br>
<br>
But, I still think it’s wrong and makes the server worse. Plat dealers make it easy for anyone that wants to take advantage of the No Drop rules here to start up a character and have Planer or better gear on day 1. No working their way up; often no bother with really learning their class. Most don’t care about an ingame community beyond a few people that think like them: push as high as you can as fast as you can. I don’t care about the server economy, but I do care about the server community. The bazaar made it too easy for these plat dealers to thrive and for these jerks to flock to this server.<br>
<br>
Buying platinum helps keep the dealers in business so they are available for even more jerks to jump to FV and gear up. Because of the high level gear, they are in their 50s fast and we all wind up dealing with them. Trains, profanity in shouts, and just all around jerks. There are a LOT more on this server than there used to be. I started on this server with a half elf warrior. At one point I tried to switch to another server because I wanted more than one character. Anyone who’s played on other servers knows the crowd on FV a year ago was much more mature than on other servers. That’s what brought me back. Now FV is sliding down. It’s too convenient for them to jump over here and get uber. People can buy a naked character, gear it up, and go play. Tell me it doesn’t affect anyone when you are grouped with a 60 cleric that doesn’t know what all their spells do or an epic monk that doesn’t really understand FD. <br>
<br>
So what do you think? Some people who think ebaying is wrong still think buying platinum is ok. I know this isn’t the only factor. Am I overreacting when I get mad?  Am I stupid for thinking this has a negative impact on the quality of the game for people who play on FV? Has it ever affected you?  <br>
